nagios-virt by Richard W.M. Jones <rjones@redhat.com>
----------------------------------------------------------------------
$Id: INSTALL,v 1.1 2007/09/25 11:53:44 rjones Exp $

Prerequisites
-------------

* gcc
* GNU-ish programming environment (we depend on some
	_GNU_SOURCE features of glibc)
* libvirt (http://libvirt.org/)
* libxml2 (http://xmlsoft.org/)
* nagios (http://nagios.org/)

Build
-----

First run:

  ./configure

There are a number of options you can give to ./configure.  To see
them, do ./configure --help.

Then do:

  make

To carry out some checks that nagios-virt is likely to work, you can do:

  make check

Install
-------

As root, do:

  make install
